Yeah, thank you.

6
00:00:18,740 --> 00:00:21,270
Is this Mikhail's residence?

7
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:25,000
Go do some shopping at
Dick Sakura, by the station.

8
00:00:25,220 --> 00:00:27,750
At check out, give the cashier this card.

9
00:00:30,530 --> 00:00:32,500
Please come this way, sir.

10
00:02:01,970 --> 00:02:07,020
Strategy x And x Scheme

11
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:14,320
There are more people this time.

12
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:20,870
I wonder if there's anyone I know.

13
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:23,910
Yo.

14
00:02:24,190 --> 00:02:26,550
Last year, you had your way with us.

15
00:02:26,550 --> 00:02:28,980
But that won't happen again.

16
00:02:28,980 --> 00:02:32,170
We've undergone some hellish training.

17
00:02:32,730 --> 00:02:36,040
Our teamwork is perfect now.

18
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,800
Thank you for coming!

19
00:02:42,170 --> 00:02:46,800
This year, 1,489 applicants
have made it this far,

20
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:52,060
but the Phase Two examiner has asked me
to trim that number to about 300.

21
00:02:52,770 --> 00:02:54,760
As for the exam...

22
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:56,840
There are two hours before lunch.

23
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,690
Defeat five people before then.

24
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,950
Grab their tags when you defeat them,

25
00:03:00,950 --> 00:03:03,200
and see me when you have all five.

26
00:03:03,510 --> 00:03:05,320
I'll wait on the other side of the door.

27
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:06,500
Got it?

28
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:08,580
As soon as I shut the door,

29
00:03:08,580 --> 00:03:10,580
you may start.

30
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:17,840
Every stage of the exam should be like this...

31
00:03:18,770 --> 00:03:22,630
You've gotta be strong to be a Hunter.

32
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:31,670
Oh, you're here!

33
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:32,620
Killu—

34
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:35,860
Sucks for you.

35
00:03:36,290 --> 00:03:38,440
I'm the only one passing this year.

36
00:03:39,490 --> 00:03:41,820
He's totally out of our league...

37
00:03:42,970 --> 00:03:46,120
So that's what it takes to
become a top Hunter...

38
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:50,640
This will be the last time I
attempt the Hunter Exam...

39
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,950
We finally have our first applicant.

40
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:04,160
That took an hour and a half.

41
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:05,680
What happened to everyone else?

42
00:04:06,310 --> 00:04:07,330
They're all asleep.

43
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:12,910
It took me a while to collect all their tags.

44
00:04:17,430 --> 00:04:19,300
Is there going to be a second stage?

45
00:04:21,910 --> 00:04:24,390
That won't be necessary.

46
00:04:24,390 --> 00:04:27,680
He's demonstrated his skill.

47
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:31,320
Killua, denizen of the darkness...

48
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:35,000
He's returned much stronger.

49
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:39,030
Applicant 1219, Killua-kun.

50
00:04:39,030 --> 00:04:39,960
Yeah.

51
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:41,460
You've passed

52
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:44,480
the Hunter Exam!

53
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:52,190
Welcome back, Killua.

54
00:04:52,190 --> 00:04:53,370
How was the exam?

55
00:04:53,370 --> 00:04:55,520
I passed it in no time, naturally.

56
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,440
Yay!

57
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:02,030
Sorry to interrupt your celebration,
but look at these spell cards.

58
00:05:03,690 --> 00:05:05,040
Wow...

59
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,990
There's even an S-rank card!

60
00:05:06,990 --> 00:05:09,110
How much can we sell it for?

61
00:05:09,110 --> 00:05:12,010
Oh, let's go ask around!

62
00:05:12,010 --> 00:05:14,540
No, we should use it wisely.

63
00:05:15,050 --> 00:05:16,740
So what should we do?

64
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:19,110
Well, I guess it's safe to hold on to it.

65
00:05:19,530 --> 00:05:21,190
With all these defensive spells,

66
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:23,300
we don't need to worry
about it getting stolen.

67
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,690
Have you tried any of these?

68
00:05:25,690 --> 00:05:27,650
Just Blackout Curtain.

69
00:05:27,650 --> 00:05:28,780
What?

70
00:05:28,780 --> 00:05:30,930
If you have all these cards,
you should use them...

71
00:05:31,290 --> 00:05:33,730
Start by using this one.

72
00:05:33,730 --> 00:05:38,020
You can choose a player you've
met before, and talk to them.

73
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:38,020
Contact
Communicate with one target
player (encountered within the
game) via your Book.
(Connection maintained for
a maximum of 3 minutes.
May only be broken by
player who used this card.)
[LR][NORM]

74
00:05:38,450 --> 00:05:40,090
Who should we talk to?

75
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:42,030
We won't know until we see who's available.

76
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:44,030
Contact on!

77
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:51,660
Oh, I see a lot of names.

78
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:55,840
Hey, Gon...

79
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:57,560
When did you run into him?

80
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,450
Huh?

81
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:05,010
Chrollo Lucilfer

82
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:04,570
Chrollo?

83
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:07,120
Who's Chrollo?

84
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:10,210
I haven't seen Chrollo inside the game.

85
00:06:10,210 --> 00:06:13,050
Does that mean you guys passed
each other without noticing?

86
00:06:13,050 --> 00:06:14,640
Huh? What are you talking about?

87
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:16,260
That doesn't make sense.

88
00:06:16,260 --> 00:06:19,020
Kurapika sealed his Nen.

89
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:22,900
Yeah, and you have to use
Nen to enter the game.

90
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:24,620
Who's Kurapika?!

91
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:26,320
That only leaves...

92
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,630
Let me in on this!

93
00:06:33,110 --> 00:06:35,330
I get it. So that's what's going on.

94
00:06:36,910 --> 00:06:38,250
Hey, Shal...

95
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:40,430
Stop laughing, and explain
what this is about.

96
00:06:40,430 --> 00:06:41,830
Sorry about that.

97
00:06:41,830 --> 00:06:44,710
Chrollo Lucilfer

98
00:06:43,020 --> 00:06:44,710
This probably isn't the boss.

99
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:47,840
He hasn't purged the Nen from his body.

100
00:06:49,030 --> 00:06:50,200
Purging Nen?

101
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,090
It's very doable.

102
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:52,050
Seriously?

103
00:06:52,050 --> 00:06:53,170
Of course!

104
00:06:53,170 --> 00:06:54,960
If you can place Nen on others,

105
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:57,350
it's not unreasonable to think
Nen can be removed, as well.

106
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:02,100
Does that mean Chrollo has removed
Kurapika's Nen, and entered the game?

107
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,860
Why would he be here?

108
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:05,500
I'm not sure,

109
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,670
but we should probably let Kurapika know.

110
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:10,600
I'll leave the game real quick.

111
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,740
You can use a spell card to leave.

112
00:07:13,570 --> 00:07:14,800
Save it.

113
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,440
I can be out and back in four hours.

114
00:07:18,350 --> 00:07:20,240
I should have realized this sooner...

115
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:25,000
Yorknew City                                        Greed Island

116
00:07:21,210 --> 00:07:25,000
This island is directly east of Yorknew City.

117
00:07:27,410 --> 00:07:29,340
East is the direction to go.

118
00:07:29,340 --> 00:07:32,190
You will find one who awaits you.

119
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:33,800
I see.

120
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:36,600
So the boss came here to find
someone to purge that Nen.

121
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:40,760
The boss arrived the same way we did,

122
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,260
but then Razor kicked him out.

123
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:44,790
That was when he realized
this was Greed Island.

124
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:47,840
But since the boss can't use Nen,

125
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:50,400
he can't enter the island
via the usual channels.

126
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:54,160
So he must have hired someone
to come to this island for him.

127
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:58,750
He had them use his name
as a hidden message to us.

128
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:04,010
The one who can purge this
Nen is on Greed Island.

129
00:08:06,060 --> 00:08:08,550
Change in plans again...

130
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:10,860
Let's bring everyone else here.

131
00:08:10,860 --> 00:08:14,290
Yes, we'll all start looking
for this Nen exorcist.

132
00:08:14,290 --> 00:08:16,170
I have a small correction.

133
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:20,990
You're...

134
00:08:20,990 --> 00:08:21,900
Hisoka!

135
00:08:22,820 --> 00:08:26,640
It was my idea to use Chrollo's name.

136
00:08:27,290 --> 00:08:30,690
Because I didn't know you could
enter any name you like

137
00:08:30,690 --> 00:08:33,710
until I was already inside...

138
00:08:34,970 --> 00:08:36,390
You should praise my initiative.

139
00:08:36,790 --> 00:08:40,580
Since I helped you understand Chrollo's message.

140
00:08:40,940 --> 00:08:43,010
Ah, so that's what this is about.

141
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:46,330
I'm dying to kill you right here and now,

142
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:48,260
but I'll let the boss do that.

143
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:53,550
Well, if anything comes up,
use Contact to get in touch.

144
00:08:54,070 --> 00:08:57,020
If I learn anything new, I'll let you know.

145
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,280
Bye.

146
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:05,230
So the boss hired Hisoka...

147
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:07,820
He probably didn't have much
choice, but it's still weird.

148
00:09:07,820 --> 00:09:11,060
And his reward is probably a duel,
once the boss is cleansed.

149
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:14,150
But now, it's only a matter of time

150
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:17,810
until the boss comes back!

151
00:09:20,430 --> 00:09:21,910
I doubt it.

152
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,700
I would know at once

153
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:28,660
if Nen I placed on a spider
had been removed.

154
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:33,370
So when you chose your power, you
knew something like this might happen?

155
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:34,810
Of course...

156
00:09:35,140 --> 00:09:37,230
If you're able to place Nen on others,

157
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:40,350
it only makes sense to assume

158
00:09:40,350 --> 00:09:42,810
that one can also remove Nen.

159
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:46,500
Well, now you know.

160
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:48,060
What you do from here is up to you.

161
00:09:48,450 --> 00:09:50,010
Thanks for taking the trouble.

162
00:09:50,330 --> 00:09:51,340
You have my gratitude.

163
00:09:55,690 --> 00:09:56,740
Did you need anything?

164
00:09:59,410 --> 00:10:01,690
What am I...

165
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:04,430
What am I supposed to do this month?

166
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:06,570
Tell me...

167
00:10:07,150 --> 00:10:08,950
What should I do?

168
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:12,150
It'll be fine. Let me handle...

169
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:13,710
What could you possibly know?

170
00:10:14,270 --> 00:10:17,990
You have no idea what's going
to happen to us now!

171
00:10:18,610 --> 00:10:19,990
Neon... I need Neon!

172
00:10:19,990 --> 00:10:21,800
Restore Neon at once!

173
00:10:24,930 --> 00:10:28,020
Damn! Why did this happen?

174
00:10:31,290 --> 00:10:32,870
I wonder what's wrong...

175
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:37,000
Why did it stop working?

176
00:10:39,070 --> 00:10:39,990
See ya.

177
00:10:43,410 --> 00:10:46,430
Looks like it's not the real Chrollo.

178
00:10:46,430 --> 00:10:47,500
Oh...

179
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:50,380
Kurapika was pretty calm about it.

180
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:53,460
Like he wasn't concerned or just didn't care.

181
00:10:54,130 --> 00:10:57,010
Well, it sounds like you
got worried for nothing.

182
00:10:57,010 --> 00:11:00,260
Now it's time to focus on yourselves.

183
