Up for a trade?

256
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:53,810
I have #66, Witch's Diet Pill,
and #17, VIP Multi-Pass.

257
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,430
You can talk it over with your friends.

258
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:58,070
What do you think?

259
00:14:04,650 --> 00:14:08,700
Another player has used Contact to reach you.

260
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:10,470
It's Tsezgerra.

261
00:14:10,470 --> 00:14:11,630
You again?

262
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:13,780
Interested in trading your

263
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:16,730
Breath of Archangel for our Patch of Forest?

264
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:18,210
It's an SS-rank card.

265
00:14:18,410 --> 00:14:19,680
No way.

266
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:22,870
I've already said I won't
deal with you people.

267
00:14:22,870 --> 00:14:25,020
What if I throw in a Clone?

268
00:14:25,020 --> 00:14:27,720
I'm telling you that there's no deal here.

269
00:14:28,060 --> 00:14:31,030
You already have ninety-two different cards.

270
00:14:31,660 --> 00:14:32,930
All that's left

271
00:14:32,930 --> 00:14:35,890
are the cards monopolized
by other players, yes?

272
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:40,140
Actually, we have ninety-five...

273
00:14:40,140 --> 00:14:44,110
And you probably have many items
that you haven't used Gain on yet.

274
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:50,490
It's possible that Breath of Archangel
is the final card you need.

275
00:14:51,370 --> 00:14:56,440
If we give that to you, we'll lose.

276
00:14:58,140 --> 00:14:59,870
Stop playing dumb.

277
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:03,010
I know that you're monopolizing

278
00:15:03,010 --> 00:15:07,130
both Breath of Archangel and Night Jade.

279
00:15:07,130 --> 00:15:09,290
This game isn't over yet.

280
00:15:09,290 --> 00:15:10,130
I see.

281
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:12,480
Good luck, then.

282
00:15:12,930 --> 00:15:15,420
But we'll never let you have these cards.

283
00:15:15,420 --> 00:15:17,390
What if I offer three cards?

284
00:15:17,620 --> 00:15:21,110
We'll give you Patch of Forest,

285
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,670
Patch of Forest
The entrance to an enormous
forest known as the Mountain
God's Garden. Many species
exist only in this forest.
All are friendly to humans.

286
00:15:20,670 --> 00:15:22,420
Hidden Hollow
Upon entering and exiting hollow,
player will be transported to a
desolate location. However, player can
return to original location
without spending any money.

287
00:15:21,110 --> 00:15:22,870
Hidden Hollow,

288
00:15:22,420 --> 00:15:24,270
Palmtop Dragon
As the name implies, this dragon
fits on your palm. Willingly obeys
its master. If raised lovingly,
it can learn to speak.

289
00:15:22,870 --> 00:15:24,270
and Palmtop Dragon.

290
00:15:25,340 --> 00:15:29,280
And you only have to give us Night Jade,
not Breath of Archangel.

291
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:33,430
We'd be giving you one SS-rank
card and two S-rank cards,

292
00:15:33,430 --> 00:15:35,750
while you'd only give up one A-rank card.

293
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,790
I believe this deal is too good to pass up.

294
00:15:40,010 --> 00:15:41,890
Give us some time to discuss this.

295
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:44,370
Just to be clear, this is our final offer.

296
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:47,110
We won't accept any further negotiation.

297
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:48,500
Book.

298
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:51,510
It's gotta be a trap.

299
00:15:51,510 --> 00:15:53,190
That offer's too good.

300
00:15:53,190 --> 00:15:55,620
Tsezgerra is a careful man.

301
00:15:55,620 --> 00:15:57,680
He wouldn't try to pick a fight.

302
00:15:58,030 --> 00:16:01,610
But at the same time, he would
never make a losing deal.

303
00:16:01,870 --> 00:16:06,190
Breath of Archangel
An angel who can cure any mortal
injury or terminal disease with one breath.
However, angel will appear only once.

304
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:03,930
Meaning that he thinks

305
00:16:03,930 --> 00:16:06,190
he can obtain a Breath of Archangel.

306
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:11,110
Does that mean they've assembled
all forty spell card types?

307
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:12,500
It's possible.

308
00:16:12,810 --> 00:16:16,200
So they're waiting for Gain to be
used on a Breath of Archangel.

309
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:22,710
Night Jade
A jewel blessed by the devil.
When the holder is in danger,
peril will be shifted to another.

310
00:16:16,710 --> 00:16:19,050
On the other hand, Night Jade is a card

311
00:16:19,050 --> 00:16:20,660
that we monopolized through hard work.

312
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:23,500
If one of the cards were to be destroyed,

313
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:26,960
one of our jade jewels would
automatically turn into a card.

314
00:16:27,850 --> 00:16:32,080
Which means the A-rank
Night Jade is much harder

315
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:35,220
for them to get than the
SS-rank Breath of Archangel.

316
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:38,150
This is a gamble.

317
00:16:39,370 --> 00:16:42,730
Witch's Love Potion
If player kisses a pill before
feeding it to a target, target will
become beholden to player.
Each pill will remain effective
for one week. Each bottle
contains 500 pills.

318
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:42,730
VIP Multi-Pass
Present this pass to gain
entry into any location.
Contains 1000 passes.

319
00:16:45,810 --> 00:16:46,590
Book.

320
00:16:47,860 --> 00:16:48,620
See ya.

321
00:16:56,260 --> 00:16:58,430
That was uneventful.

322
00:16:58,430 --> 00:17:00,180
Kind of disappointing.

323
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,100
I was so nervous...

324
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:05,250
But now we've gathered
seven types, in three days!

325
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:07,450
We're making decent progress.

326
00:17:07,840 --> 00:17:09,930
Okay, let's keep this up.

327
00:17:10,340 --> 00:17:13,920
Are there any other events in the city
for getting restricted slot cards?

328
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:17,260
Hmm... I think there are...

329
00:17:18,340 --> 00:17:20,090
Prizes from the slot machines?

330
00:17:20,570 --> 00:17:23,020
Should've expected as much from
Dorias, the City of Gambling.

331
00:17:23,260 --> 00:17:26,200
You have a 0.01% chance of winning.

332
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:28,000
That's one in ten thousand tries.

333
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,540
So it all comes down to luck.

334
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:31,230
Pretty risky.

335
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:33,740
I know, Gon!

336
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:34,660
Use that dice!

337
00:17:35,050 --> 00:17:36,260
This is it...

338
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:38,160
If we get Good Luck, we can win!

339
00:17:38,430 --> 00:17:40,420
But if you get Bad Luck,

340
00:17:40,420 --> 00:17:42,740
something bad will happen that cancels out

341
00:17:42,740 --> 00:17:44,300
everything good that's happened.

342
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:47,170
There's only a one in twenty
chance of getting Bad Luck.

343
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:50,470
There!

344
00:17:51,510 --> 00:17:53,550
Next, we try the slot machine!

345
00:17:57,190 --> 00:17:59,010
Awesome! One try!

346
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:01,390
Rainbow Diamond
A diamond that glitters like
a rainbow. If this diamond
is presented when proposing,
you will never be turned down.

347
00:17:59,500 --> 00:18:01,390
A Rainbow Diamond! Score!

348
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,260
That's what I thought...

349
00:18:03,260 --> 00:18:06,640
This die is the key to winning in this city.

350
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:10,950
But if you roll Bad Luck, it could be scary.

351
00:18:10,950 --> 00:18:12,520
Don't worry.

352
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:14,180
It can't kill me...

353
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:18,160
Oh, no! A slot machine exploded!

354
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:20,220
I knew something was wrong.

355
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:22,910
That guy hit the jackpot five times in a row.

356
00:18:23,170 --> 00:18:25,400
And he was acting weird...

357
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:27,310
He kept rolling a funny-looking die.

358
00:18:27,910 --> 00:18:31,290
Yikes, his face is mush...

359
00:18:32,670 --> 00:18:35,300
Anyway, let's make the trade.

360
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:40,090
Yeah, we want to get cards of rank S
and above as quickly as possible.

361
00:18:40,460 --> 00:18:41,890
Yeah.

362
00:18:41,890 --> 00:18:44,060
As for cards rank A and below...

363
00:18:47,210 --> 00:18:48,080
Roll.

364
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:50,310
S-Spare me...

365
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:53,040
This is only your third time.

366
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,190
You'll be fine.

367
00:18:54,190 --> 00:18:59,220
I-I know someone who got
Bad Luck on the first roll and died!

368
00:18:59,220 --> 00:19:01,930
If I roll Bad Luck,

369
00:19:01,930 --> 00:19:05,860
I'll be hit for every Good Luck
that the other players rolled!

370
00:19:05,860 --> 00:19:07,120
Not my problem.

371
00:19:07,530 --> 00:19:08,330
Roll.

372
00:19:08,330 --> 00:19:11,150
Or would you rather die right now?

373
00:19:19,650 --> 00:19:20,680
Come on...

374
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:26,840
See?

375
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:29,270
It's pretty rare to get Bad Luck.

376
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:32,020
Now we use the Lottery card.

377
00:19:33,370 --> 00:19:37,690
We want #75, Lucky Alexandrite.

378
00:19:38,290 --> 00:19:41,280
If you obtain one, we'll set you free.

379
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:43,240
C-Come on...

380
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,630
Lottery on!

381
00:19:47,230 --> 00:19:47,940
Well?

382
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:50,430
#76!

383
00:19:50,430 --> 00:19:52,270
So close!

384
00:19:52,610 --> 00:19:54,270
Your luck sucks.

385
00:19:54,270 --> 00:19:56,020
Okay, one more time!

386
00:19:56,020 --> 00:19:57,770
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

387
00:19:57,770 --> 00:20:01,980
Time for Motarike-kun to
show us what he's got!

388
00:20:05,060 --> 00:20:06,440
No good, huh?

389
00:20:07,730 --> 00:20:08,700
Hey, Gen.

390
00:20:08,990 --> 00:20:10,930
Should we make the first move?

391
00:20:11,350 --> 00:20:14,520
I already told you that combat
should be our last resort.

392
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:15,440
It's too early for that.

393
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:18,940
No, we're trying to stay
one step ahead of them.

394
00:20:19,430 --> 00:20:21,530
Though, once we commit,

395
00:20:21,530 --> 00:20:24,190
further negotiation will be impossible.

396
00:20:24,670 --> 00:20:26,200
What do you have in mind?

397
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:30,950
Tax Collector's Gauntlet
When equipped, player has
the ability to cast Levy. But
each cast will destroy a random
card from player's restricted
slots. (Cannot use Levy if
restricted slots are empty.)

398
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:28,820
We use Tax Collector's Gauntlet,

399
00:20:28,820 --> 00:20:30,950
combined with Risky Dice.

400
00:20:32,890 --> 00:20:34,380
I understand.

401
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:37,990
We use this to steal eight cards
from them immediately...

402
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,460
But it's definitely dangerous.

403
00:20:40,870 --> 00:20:43,870
If someone rolls Bad Luck, they'll probably die.

404
00:20:44,450 --> 00:20:48,030
But this job is too important to leave to them.

405
00:20:48,690 --> 00:20:49,470
We can do this!

406
00:20:49,860 --> 00:20:52,430
We've come this far.
Let's clear the game.

407
00:20:55,620 --> 00:20:56,730
Hey, Gen...

408
00:20:57,270 --> 00:20:58,460
What are you up to?

409
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:00,260
I've told you this many times.

410
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:04,630
When taking a risk, we three share the danger.

411
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:18,030
It's Tsezgerra.

412
00:21:18,030 --> 00:21:19,370
Have you reached a decision?

413
00:21:19,370 --> 00:21:21,860
Okay, you have a deal.

414
00:21:27,030 --> 00:21:27,890
I can do this...

415
00:21:28,550 --> 00:21:30,470
One more time!

416
00:21:30,470 --> 00:21:32,270
I said I can do this,

417
00:21:32,270 --> 00:21:34,690
so I'm gonna do it!

418
00:21:37,410 --> 00:21:41,350
Okay, let's move on to the next city!

419
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:47,440
Gon's team has begun
working to beat the game.

420
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:50,470
The story is nearing its climax.

421
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:08,260
G.I. Tutorial

422
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:04,900
Coming up, it's the
Greed Island Tutorial!

423
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:09,390
Today, we introduce the card Lottery.

424
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:18,870
Lottery
Change this card
into a random item card.
[SR][NORM]

425
00:23:09,390 --> 00:23:13,370
When you use this card,
it changes into a random card.

426
00:23:13,370 --> 00:23:16,360
That's why it's effective to use with Risky Dice.

427
00:23:19,420 --> 00:23:21,250
Continue!

428
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:27,880
Next time: 15 X 15.

429
00:23:28,270 --> 00:23:30,130
Hey, Killua, is this fifteen?

430
00:23:30,130 --> 00:23:31,470
What did you think it was?

431
00:23:31,470 --> 00:23:32,810
One five.

432
00:23:32,810 --> 00:23:34,400
Cute, huh...
